&gt; &gt; &gt; 3) An Eclipse setting to set #2
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; It sounds like everyone who is requesting this feature is a user of
&gt; &gt; JDave,
&gt; &gt; &gt; and a quick Eclipse setting would give them everything they want.
&gt; &gt; It would
&gt; &gt; &gt; also allow users of other JUnit-based frameworks to do similar things.
&gt; &gt; &gt; Thoughts?
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt;    David Saff
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; On Wed, Jan 14, 2009 at 3:42 AM, Lasse Koskela &lt;lasse.koskela@&gt;wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; Hi David, Tuomas,
