&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; With that said, I don&#39;t think the increase in complexity that we&#39;re
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; talking about here is all that big. If you don&#39;t specify a runner
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; (non-static inner class), one is inherited from one level up
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; (declaring class).
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; Again, I might be biased but I sure would like to be able to run
&gt; just
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; one of the tests.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
