&gt; feature
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; will be
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; worth a 20% increase in complexity for everyone who needs to
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; understand the
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; default running rules?
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;    David Saff
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; On Wed, Dec 31, 2008 at 3:08 AM, tuomaskarkkainenri &lt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; tuomaskarkkainenri@&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; hey David,
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; i uploaded the patch as a file,
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt;
&gt; http://f1.grp.yahoofs.com/v1/cBhbSQYycXqWtmfu6mA5iis6I67Qo0Itb3lfEH-tMTD2PqfQBWFNQwiqbje7jxu7yGSHFHijEoZPnMvQpZtq0gohmbE9pzSYXRseJ5ewyt0/nonstaticinnerclasses.patch
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; or if that link is relative to my session it&#39;s
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; nonstaticinnerclasses.patch under files here in Yahoo Groups.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; in JUnit4 speak:
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; public class RegularJunit4 {
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;  public class NonStaticInnerClass {
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;    @Test
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;    public void testMethod() {
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;    }
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;  }
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; }
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; running testMethod() is not possible since NonStaticInnerClass
&gt; &gt; cannot
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; be instantiated from the outside.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; in JDave:
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;  @RunWith(JDaveRunner.class)
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;  public static class ASpec extends Specification&lt;Void&gt; {
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;    public class AContext {
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;      public void aBehavior() {}
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;    }
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;  }
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; AContext is instantiated by SpecRunner which JDaveRunner
&gt; &gt; delegates to.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; When I run this with current JUnit,
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; AllDefaultPossibilitiesBuilder#runnerForClass(final Class&lt;?&gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; testClass) picks out the @RunWith annotation and uses that to
&gt; &gt; run my
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; spec(test class).
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; However if I want to run just a single behavior (test
&gt; method) from
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; this spec for example from Eclipse.  Eclipse tells JUnit to
&gt; &gt; run class
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; ASpec.AContext and method aBehavior JUnit then sees what
&gt; &gt; builder it
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; should use for AContext, and doesn&#39;t find the annotation
&gt; there and
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; tries to use the regular JUnit4 builder and since it&#39;s a JDave
&gt; &gt; spec it
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; fails to run.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; What I want to do is: in case AllDefaultPossibilitiesBuilder
&gt; &gt; notices
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; that the TestClass is a non-static member class, which it has no
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; chance of being able run anyway, it checks whether the
&gt; &gt; declaring class
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; of the testclass would be able to run it instead.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; In the case of JDave, the declaring class would have the
&gt; @RunWith
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; annotation, and with the Filter created by FilterRequest,
&gt; &gt; JDave can
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; then choose which Context and Spec it should actually allow to
&gt; &gt; run.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; br,
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; Tuomas
