&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; tuomaskarkkainenri@&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;   I participate in JDave (http://jdave.org). A BDD framework
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; for Java
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; that takes advantage of JUnit for example for Eclipse
&gt; &gt; integration.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; We have tests in non-static inner classes of our test
&gt; classes.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; These
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; run wonderfully using the @RunWith annotation and our own
&gt; &gt; runner.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; however, for individual tests, this doesn&#39;t work. What I
&gt; would
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; like
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; to do is that AllDefaultPossibilitiesBuilder would check
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; whether or
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; not the test class is a non static member class. if it is,
&gt; &gt; then I
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; would grab the runner of the declaring class instead.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; I made a patch implementing this. I will try to attach it.
